        <ExplanationTxt>APPLICATIONS FOR GRANTS ARE RECEIVED VIA EMAIL USING THE GRANT TEMPLATE PROVIDED ON THE FOUNDATION'S WEBSITE. THE INFORMATION IS THEN MAINTAINED IN AN EXCEL DATABASE AND VETTED WITH THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE PRESIDENT TYPICALLY SPEAKS DIRECTLY WITH THE APPLICANT AND/OR THE PROSTHETIST TO DETERMINE COST FOR THE PROSTHETIC REQUESTED. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS THEN VOTES ON THE GRANTS TO BE GRANTED. THE FOUNDATION THEN MAKES PAYMENT DIRECTLY TO THE PROSTHETIST FOR COSTS OF THE DEVICE AS WELL AS THE NONPROFIT CAMP FOR SCHOLARSHIPS AWARDED IN THE HAF KIDS' CAMP SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM.</ExplanationTxt>
